    public interface SystemName
extends com.vmware.vapi.bindings.Service, SystemNameTypes, com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService
    The SystemName interface provides methods to enumerate system names of appliance backups. This interface was added in vSphere API 6.7.

    • Method Detail

      • list

        SystemName.ListInvocation list(LocationSpec locSpec)
        Returns a list of system names for which backup archives exist under locSpec. This method was added in vSphere API 6.7.

        Invocation Result:
        list of system names The return value will contain identifiers for the resource type: com.vmware.appliance.recovery.backup.system_name.

        Parameters:
        locSpec - LocationSpec Structure
        Returns:
        instance of SystemName.ListInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described list operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        NotFound - if locSpec doesn't refer to an existing location on the backup server.
        Error - if any error occurs during the execution of the operation.
